                                         CAPE TOWN - Police are still searching for the suspect responsible for the fatal shooting of a train commuter in Lansdowne. The man was caught in a gun battle between criminals and police at the Crawford train station. The police's Frederick van Wyk said: “Anyone with any information that could lead to the arrest of the suspect or suspects is kindly requested to contact Lansdowne police on 021 700 900 or crime stop on 0860 10111.”